00:40:45,651 --> 00:40:48,571
Time for Madam Amy's vitamins.

449
00:40:55,077 --> 00:40:58,122
This is Karen Ross. 81452.

450
00:40:58,289 --> 00:41:03,586
That is KR81452. 
Houston, Travis, do you read?

451
00:41:04,336 --> 00:41:09,049
<i>Karen Ross, 81452. 
Houston, Travis, do you read?</i>

452
00:41:09,216 --> 00:41:14,096
I read and see you, Dr. Ross. 
Congratulations on crossing the border.

453
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:18,058
<i>I'm picking up a signal 
from the laser's power pack.</i>

454
00:41:18,184 --> 00:41:20,936
Excellent. Wherever the laser is, 
Charles should be too.

455
00:41:21,103 --> 00:41:25,524
Let's hope so. Tomorrow we enter the 
rainforest at the base of the volcanic range.

456
00:41:25,691 --> 00:41:30,779
<i>Good. Karen, I've had those images 
of that creature analyzed. Rudy.</i>

457
00:41:37,244 --> 00:41:40,331
<i>What's W? 
- My primatologist tells me it's something new.</i>

458
00:41:40,498 --> 00:41:42,708
<i>He doesn't know what, 
but it's gorilla-like.</i>

459
00:41:42,875 --> 00:41:44,752
Are you sufficiently armed?

460
00:41:44,919 --> 00:41:47,713
- Do you have enough manpower? 
<i>- Yes.</i>

461
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:51,592
Good. The bad news is Geo-thermal. 
You've got to hurry.

462
00:41:51,759 --> 00:41:55,638
That region in the Virungas is bad. 
Sometimes the volcanic activity...

463
00:41:55,804 --> 00:41:58,766
<i>is breaking out of the graph. 
The region's going to blow.</i>

464
00:41:58,933 --> 00:42:01,519
<i>Could be a week, could be sooner. 
Dr. Ross...</i>

465
00:42:01,685 --> 00:42:03,896
- What the hell...? 
- Watch out!

466
00:42:04,063 --> 00:42:07,524
No, dammit! Not again!

467
00:42:07,858 --> 00:42:10,194
Oh. I'm terribly sorry.

468
00:42:13,739 --> 00:42:15,366
It's destroyed.

469
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:19,912
It's completely destroyed.

470
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:31,942
It's Amy's medical supplies. 
They can't get wet.

471
00:43:55,674 --> 00:43:59,511
Beautiful boats. 
Money's a wonderful thing.

472
00:43:59,678 --> 00:44:01,597
Give her the banana with the dope inside?

473
00:44:01,764 --> 00:44:05,225
Yes, he gave her the banana 
with the dope inside.

474
00:44:05,392 --> 00:44:08,604
I know. Shitty Peter. I know.

475
00:44:08,771 --> 00:44:11,065
Hey, what's this?

476
00:44:12,858 --> 00:44:14,401
Oh.

477
00:44:14,985 --> 00:44:17,363
All <i>the</i> leaves are brown

478
00:44:17,529 --> 00:44:20,282
<i>And the sky is gray</i>

479
00:44:20,449 --> 00:44:22,910
<i>I've been for a walk</i>

480
00:44:23,077 --> 00:44:24,995
<i>On</i> a <i>winters day</i>

481
00:44:25,162 --> 00:44:26,914
<i>On a winters day</i>

482
00:44:27,081 --> 00:44:30,626
<i>I'd be safe and warm</i>

483
00:44:30,793 --> 00:44:34,713
<i>If I was in L.A.</i>

484
00:44:34,838 --> 00:44:38,550
<i>- California dreaming 
- California dreaming</i>

485
00:44:38,717 --> 00:44:42,471
<i>On such a winters day</i>

486
00:44:42,638 --> 00:44:46,975
<i>Stopped into a church</i>

487
00:44:57,611 --> 00:44:59,863
Watch out for the rock!

488
00:45:01,115 --> 00:45:02,241
Whoa!

489
00:45:03,784 --> 00:45:05,327
Hang on!

490
00:45:24,012 --> 00:45:29,226
- What is this Zinj, Mr. Homolka? 
- I don't know what you're talking about.

491
00:45:29,393 --> 00:45:32,771
It's been believed that King Solomon 
had a diamond mine in the Congo...

492
00:45:32,938 --> 00:45:34,398
in a city called Zinj.

493
00:45:34,815 --> 00:45:36,525
Diamonds?

494
00:45:39,611 --> 00:45:43,574
I suppose there's no point 
in playing stupid.

495
00:45:43,741 --> 00:45:48,662
We shall arrive there together, 
we shall all be rich.

496
00:45:48,829 --> 00:45:51,623
That's fine with me. 
Except there's no Zinj.

497
00:45:51,749 --> 00:45:54,960
Half the safaris that have gone in looking 
never made it back.

498
00:45:55,127 --> 00:45:56,920
The other half came back with nothing.

499
00:45:57,087 --> 00:46:01,759
Yes, but we have a trumping card 
that they did not have.

500
00:46:01,925 --> 00:46:05,679
- We do? 
- We do. That gorilla...

501
00:46:06,221 --> 00:46:08,348
- knows where it is. 
- What?

502
00:46:08,474 --> 00:46:10,184
The gorilla?

503
00:46:10,309 --> 00:46:14,605
As a young man, 
I found a book in Soviet Georgia.

504
00:46:14,772 --> 00:46:19,234
It contained a detailed drawing 
of the city of Zinj.

505
00:46:19,776 --> 00:46:23,280
The drawing contained 
a peculiar decoration.

506
00:46:23,864 --> 00:46:26,241
An open eye.

507
00:46:26,408 --> 00:46:30,120
Later, on safari, I found this.

508
00:46:34,333 --> 00:46:36,919
It's the same symbol. Now...

509
00:46:38,587 --> 00:46:40,297
look at this.

510
00:46:42,799 --> 00:46:45,052
The gorilla drew this.

511
00:46:47,429 --> 00:46:52,309
It is the same image. It is the open eye.

512
00:46:53,018 --> 00:46:58,023
That gorilla has seen the city of Zinj.

513
00:47:01,193 --> 00:47:05,906
- And she will take us there! 
- Have you been taking your medication?

514
00:47:09,910 --> 00:47:13,163
Have your laughing, and I will have mine.

515
00:47:20,629 --> 00:47:21,880
Shit...

516
00:47:23,549 --> 00:47:26,718
- What is it? 
- The signal stopped.

517
00:47:26,885 --> 00:47:31,390
- Does that mean...? 
- It just means the signal stopped.

518
00:47:32,599 --> 00:47:34,268
I don't know what it means.

519
00:48:34,494 --> 00:48:36,163
No problem.

520
00:49:03,065 --> 00:49:04,191
Oh, my God!

521
00:49:14,660 --> 00:49:16,787
- Shoot it! 
- Amy!

522
00:49:16,953 --> 00:49:20,457
- What is it? 
- Turn the boat around, quickly.

523
00:49:23,794 --> 00:49:26,088
Agh! Aah!

524
00:49:26,797 --> 00:49:29,299
Shoot it! Oh, my God!

525
00:49:31,093 --> 00:49:33,011
Turn the boat around!

526
00:49:37,182 --> 00:49:39,059
Head for shore!

527
00:49:55,575 --> 00:49:57,411
- How is he? 
- It's just a big cut.

528
00:49:57,577 --> 00:49:59,788
- I'll stitch it up, he'll be all right. 
- Oh, God.

529
00:50:01,331 --> 00:50:04,126
- What's that? 
- A plane.

530
00:50:05,085 --> 00:50:07,462
- Good luck to them. 
- Who are they?

531
00:50:07,629 --> 00:50:11,758
I don't know, but the Zaire Air Force 
has got a piece of their ass.

532
00:50:16,179 --> 00:50:19,433
Pitch camp. Tomorrow, Mt. Mukenko.

533
00:50:39,077 --> 00:50:41,580
- She's getting excited. 
- Why, do you think?

534
00:50:41,747 --> 00:50:45,417
Somewhere on the other side of this 
mountain is where Amy was born.

535
00:51:13,445 --> 00:51:15,655
Wow, it's beautiful.

536
00:51:17,449 --> 00:51:20,452
Is this your valley, Amy? 
It is, isn't it?

537
00:51:20,619 --> 00:51:23,663
It's home. That's your home.

538
00:51:25,874 --> 00:51:30,003
Pretty jungle, that's right.

539
00:51:35,634 --> 00:51:37,135
What's she doing?

540
00:51:37,302 --> 00:51:40,889
She wants to go to the place in her heart.

541
00:51:41,056 --> 00:51:46,812
- You mean the place in your heart, Herkermer. 
- You may call me Mr. Homolka.

542
00:51:48,313 --> 00:51:50,649
Come on, Amy, let's go.

543
00:51:52,734 --> 00:51:54,611
- We've lost two porters. 
- Where'd they go?

544
00:51:54,778 --> 00:51:58,198
- Ran away. 
- And they didn't invite me?

545
00:51:58,365 --> 00:52:01,952
You want your glove? All right, sit still.

546
00:52:05,539 --> 00:52:12,045
This, as they say, is a fork in the road. 
We could go left or we could go right.

547
00:52:12,212 --> 00:52:14,381
We go the wrong way, 
we lose two or three days.

548
00:52:14,548 --> 00:52:17,175
We must follow the gorilla. 
Where she leads.

549
00:52:19,052 --> 00:52:20,637
- That would be left. 
- Best guess...

550
00:52:20,804 --> 00:52:22,806
off my last coordinates was this way.

551
00:52:22,973 --> 00:52:27,894
- That would be right. 
- Amy, Peter, <i>go</i> this way.

552
00:52:29,104 --> 00:52:34,651
Well, I don't have her passion. 
I'll follow the gorilla.

553
00:52:41,908 --> 00:52:44,953
This doesn't seem 
like the right way to me.

554
00:53:11,938 --> 00:53:13,440
Good Lord.

555
00:53:17,319 --> 00:53:21,072
- It's that plane we saw burning in 
the sky. - Who were they?

556
00:53:21,239 --> 00:53:24,868
Travis, my boss, thought I wasn't gonna 
make it. He sent another expedition.

557
00:53:24,993 --> 00:53:29,122
Tried to push too far. Looks like a rocket 
got them. There's no point going in there.

558
00:53:30,916 --> 00:53:35,253
- My God, what a waste of life. 
- We'd better keep moving.

559
00:54:34,980 --> 00:54:38,566
- Oh, shit! Somebody help me. 
- What is it?

560
00:54:38,733 --> 00:54:41,736
There's something on my... 
Like, a creature, growth or something.

561
00:54:41,903 --> 00:54:44,906
- Look. 
- Ah. That's a leech.

562
00:54:45,073 --> 00:54:48,243
- Take it off. 
- It's your leech, you take it off.

563
00:54:48,410 --> 00:54:49,828
- Need some help? 
- No.

564
00:54:49,995 --> 00:54:52,247
- Here, burn it off with this. 
- Ha-ha-ha.

565
00:54:52,414 --> 00:54:53,832
- Ha, ha. 
- Ugh.

566
00:54:53,081 --> 00:54:56,126
- Mm! 
- This is disgusting.

567
00:55:02,757 --> 00:55:04,092
Here.

568
00:55:12,642 --> 00:55:16,229
- Monroe? 
- Don't indicate you see them.

569
00:55:17,272 --> 00:55:22,610
Mizumu. The ghost tribe. 
There are probably 20 of them.

570
00:55:24,446 --> 00:55:27,532
- I only see two. 
- Yes, that's how they are.

571
00:55:27,699 --> 00:55:31,244
- Are they friendly? 
- They're sensitive. They're forest people.

572
00:55:41,629 --> 00:55:45,508
- Why are they laughing? 
- They asked who was in charge, I said I was.

573
00:55:45,675 --> 00:55:47,802
- What's so funny about that? 
- I'm black.

574
00:55:47,969 --> 00:55:50,013
I should have luggage on my head.

575
00:55:58,605 --> 00:56:00,565
He says there's a dead white man...

576
00:56:00,732 --> 00:56:03,485
in this forest with a 
symbol on his clothes.

577
00:56:08,907 --> 00:56:11,701
He's dead? Did they say he's dead?

578
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:16,706
- What does "TC" mean? 
- TraviCom. The company I work for.

579
00:56:16,873 --> 00:56:19,042
They have several levels of "dead."

580
00:56:19,209 --> 00:56:22,837
Someone's not dead 
until they're completely dead.

581
00:57:02,085 --> 00:57:05,421
They haven't moved him. 
They believe his soul has left his body.

582
00:57:05,630 --> 00:57:09,050
If they move him, his soul will be lost, 
never finding his body again.

583
00:57:09,217 --> 00:57:12,011
They're calling to his soul, 
asking it to come back.

584
00:57:39,414 --> 00:57:40,707
Where is the man?

585
00:57:54,971 --> 00:57:56,264
- It's not him. 
- Not who?

586
00:57:56,431 --> 00:57:58,850
It's Bob Driscoll. What happened to him?

587
00:57:59,017 --> 00:58:01,394
Bob? Bob?

588
00:58:01,519 --> 00:58:03,521
- Let's sit him up. 
- Who is this man?

589
00:58:03,688 --> 00:58:07,817
My company sent an expedition to 
the Virungas. This man was with them.

590
00:58:09,027 --> 00:58:10,278
Lay him over there.

591
00:58:10,445 --> 00:58:13,198
- What happened to him? 
- I don't know.

592
00:58:14,741 --> 00:58:16,242
Bob?

593
00:58:46,648 --> 00:58:48,650
- He's dead. 
- God, no.

594
00:58:57,992 --> 00:59:00,078
That region of the Congo is uninhabited.

595
00:59:00,245 --> 00:59:02,413
- Something inhabits it. 
- What did you see?

596
00:59:02,580 --> 00:59:05,291
Camp destroyed. People dead. 
A gray gorilla or something.

597
00:59:05,458 --> 00:59:07,502
- No such thing as a gray gorilla. 
- I saw one.

598
00:59:07,669 --> 00:59:10,171
- That's hard to believe. 
- Two men are unaccounted for.

599
00:59:10,338 --> 00:59:12,840
Jeffrey Weems 
and Charles Travis, my fiancé.

600
00:59:13,007 --> 00:59:14,509
- My former fiancé. 
- Former?

601
00:59:14,676 --> 00:59:16,135
We'd better get to him, then.

602
00:59:32,026 --> 00:59:34,028
- What the hell is that? 
- Perimeter alarm.

603
00:59:34,195 --> 00:59:36,531
They had it around their camp.

604
00:59:36,906 --> 00:59:39,742
But where's the camp, their equipment?

605
00:59:57,260 --> 01:00:02,015
I don't understand it. There had to be 
300 pounds of equipment.

606
01:00:02,181 --> 01:00:04,892
And the bodies. 
There's no sign of the bodies.

607
01:00:32,962 --> 01:00:35,548
- It's a dead end? 
- Maybe, maybe not.

608
01:00:46,476 --> 01:00:47,810
Yes. Bingo!

609
01:01:40,321 --> 01:01:43,658
- Son of a bitch. 
- Jesus.

610
01:01:43,825 --> 01:01:45,785
What is this?

611
01:01:47,412 --> 01:01:50,373
It is the city of Zinj...

612
01:01:52,583 --> 01:01:56,504
that I have looked for all my life.

613
01:02:02,051 --> 01:02:05,096
See, the eyes.

614
01:02:06,347 --> 01:02:08,516
It is the same.

615
01:02:11,227 --> 01:02:13,855
Kahega, guns up. Stay alert.

616
01:02:19,694 --> 01:02:22,321
Come here, Amy. Stay with me.

617
01:04:11,347 --> 01:04:16,561
First they found the diamonds, 
Solomon's men.

618
01:04:18,271 --> 01:04:21,691
A diamond mine of incredible bounty.

619
01:04:22,942 --> 01:04:29,198
Then they built the city around 
the mine, so that it should be protected.

620
01:04:29,740 --> 01:04:32,660
The savagery of the guards was legend.

621
01:04:32,827 --> 01:04:37,123
They instantly fell upon 
any thief, any transgressor.

622
01:04:37,290 --> 01:04:41,419
The diamonds flowed 
to the kingdom of Solomon.

623
01:04:41,586 --> 01:04:43,713
What happened? Why did the city die?

624
01:04:43,879 --> 01:04:46,132
- I don't know. 
- Maybe the mines ran dry.

625
01:04:46,299 --> 01:04:49,468
No! No, the diamonds are here!

626
01:04:49,635 --> 01:04:52,722
- Monroe, over here! 
- What is it?

627
01:04:56,684 --> 01:04:58,603
On the step, by the hood.

628
01:04:58,769 --> 01:05:00,646
I found this.

629
01:05:07,612 --> 01:05:09,322
Don't go in there. I'll check it out.

630
01:05:09,488 --> 01:05:13,951
- Give me a gun and a flashlight. 
- Don't be so John Wayne, you could get killed.

631
01:05:15,578 --> 01:05:18,748
Now that I've said that, 
I'm not going in there alone, either.

632
01:05:18,914 --> 01:05:21,751
- I must go. 
- Let's all look.

633
01:05:21,876 --> 01:05:23,461
I'll just stay out here with Amy.

634
01:05:23,628 --> 01:05:25,755
Not alone you won't. Kahega!

635
01:05:51,822 --> 01:05:54,617
Stay close together. Homolka...

636
01:06:01,040 --> 01:06:06,045
- Homolka! 
- The same hieroglyphics, over and over.

637
01:06:07,672 --> 01:06:11,217
- What do they mean? 
- Homolka!

638
01:06:16,639 --> 01:06:17,973
Amy, don't wander off!

639
01:06:19,100 --> 01:06:22,103
- So do you speak English? 
- Yes.

640
01:06:22,687 --> 01:06:24,897
- What's your name? 
- Claude.

641
01:06:25,064 --> 01:06:31,404
Claude? Heh. That's an unusual name for 
somebody from, um... Where are you from?

642
01:06:31,570 --> 01:06:36,283
- Mombasa. 
- It's an unusual name for Mombasa.

643
01:06:38,411 --> 01:06:41,956
- Have you ever been to Mombasa? 
- Uh, no.

644
01:06:43,791 --> 01:06:46,419
Then what do you know about it?

645
01:06:51,549 --> 01:06:53,300
I want to go home.

646
01:06:58,222 --> 01:06:59,557
Amy?

647
01:07:02,017 --> 01:07:04,103
Amy, come here.

648
01:07:04,270 --> 01:07:08,482
Where are you, girl? 
Come on, I'm not fooling around.

649
01:07:11,569 --> 01:07:12,820
Amy.

650
01:07:13,904 --> 01:07:15,489
Amy?

651
01:07:18,075 --> 01:07:21,537
Come here, girl. Amy.

652
01:07:33,883 --> 01:07:35,634
Charles!

653
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:39,555
Charlie!

654
01:07:41,599 --> 01:07:43,809
- What are those holes? 
- Lava tubes.

655
01:07:43,976 --> 01:07:46,854
Molten rock must be flowing 
through this whole place.

656
01:07:47,021 --> 01:07:49,398
This must lead to the mine.

657
01:07:50,983 --> 01:07:54,528
Please, bring a light.

658
01:07:56,655 --> 01:07:58,073
Here.

659
01:08:00,701 --> 01:08:04,205
Now here. Come on.

660
01:08:04,371 --> 01:08:07,708
Up here. No...!

661
01:08:07,875 --> 01:08:11,462
- That's not going anywhere. 
- Where could they be? What happened?

662
01:08:13,756 --> 01:08:16,967
Shit! Let's get out of 
here while we still can.

663
01:08:17,134 --> 01:08:18,135
Help me!

664
01:08:19,053 --> 01:08:21,388
- What's that? 
- Richard!

665
01:08:22,014 --> 01:08:24,975
- Richard? 
- Help me!

666
01:08:27,353 --> 01:08:28,187
- Richard! 
-

667
01:08:28,270 --> 01:08:30,648
No! Richard! Oh, my God! Something...

668
01:09:03,889 --> 01:09:05,349
- Richard. 
- Come on.

669
01:09:05,516 --> 01:09:07,601
Let's get out of here.

670
01:09:11,272 --> 01:09:14,024
- It's okay. 
- Peter.

671
01:09:28,873 --> 01:09:31,375
They're gorillas. 
They're some kind of gorillas.

672
01:09:34,044 --> 01:09:38,799
I never saw an animal move like 
that. They just... Look. They just kill.

673
01:09:38,966 --> 01:09:43,804
That's why the diamonds were never 
found. The myth of the killer ape is true.

674
01:09:43,971 --> 01:09:45,639
I can't believe it.

675
01:10:12,166 --> 01:10:14,168
<i>Bad gorillas.</i>

676
01:10:15,419 --> 01:10:18,464
Let me turn your volume down.

677
01:10:22,301 --> 01:10:24,219
Here's your lovey.

678
01:10:27,306 --> 01:10:29,058
Shh.

679
01:10:29,224 --> 01:10:33,520
<i>- It's</i> okay. 
<i>- Mother. Mother.</i>

680
01:10:33,687 --> 01:10:35,147
Yes, you're okay now.

681
01:10:44,156 --> 01:10:48,035
- See anything? 
- No, but I'm the last line of defense.

682
01:10:48,160 --> 01:10:50,829
They have sensor-operated machine pistols 
on tripods.

683
01:10:50,079 --> 01:10:53,749
Anything comes within 40 ft., 
get ready to the 4th of July.

684
01:10:53,916 --> 01:10:56,126
What can I say, you 
really know how to pack.

685
01:11:07,137 --> 01:11:09,223
- I don't see anything. 
- Put that out.

686
01:11:30,160 --> 01:11:32,079
They're testing their perimeter.

687
01:11:40,337 --> 01:11:41,755
How intelligent are they?

688
01:11:41,922 --> 01:11:44,299
Gorillas are very smart, 
but they're not aggressive.

689
01:11:44,466 --> 01:11:48,012
- These things are very aggressive. 
- I'd say they're smart. Too damn smart.

690
01:11:48,178 --> 01:11:51,140
They're out there, but what are they doing?

691
01:11:51,807 --> 01:11:53,100
Monroe!

692
01:12:51,784 --> 01:12:52,993
Get down!

693
01:13:03,796 --> 01:13:06,799
- They're gone. 
- Couple of hours until first light.

694
01:13:06,924 --> 01:13:08,967
Then we're out of here.

695
01:13:11,387 --> 01:13:16,767
Those hieroglyphics 
we saw inscribed everywhere?

696
01:13:17,267 --> 01:13:19,478
- I have translated them. 
- What do they say?

697
01:13:19,645 --> 01:13:23,690
"We are watching you."

698
01:13:37,287 --> 01:13:40,415
We must have hit some of them. 
Where are the bodies?

699
01:13:40,582 --> 01:13:42,543
- Have you seen Amy? She's gone. 
- No.

700
01:13:42,709 --> 01:13:47,381
She's joined the club, then. We've got two 
porters missing and Homolka's run off, too.

701
01:13:47,548 --> 01:13:51,385
- I'm going to find her. 
- People come first, then gorillas.

702
01:13:51,552 --> 01:13:52,886
- Do you agree? 
- Yes.

703
01:13:53,053 --> 01:13:58,016
Good. We'll retrieve our comrades, 
then we'll retrieve your missing gorilla.

704
01:13:58,183 --> 01:14:01,770
Then we'll get the hell out of here. 
Mount up!

705
01:15:10,464 --> 01:15:11,798
What's that?

706
01:15:35,822 --> 01:15:38,951
Here's the story. 
They domesticated gorillas.

707
01:15:39,117 --> 01:15:41,870
You call that 
domesticated? They're killing a man.

708
01:15:42,037 --> 01:15:46,583
They taught them to be this way. 
They bred them to violence.

709
01:15:46,708 --> 01:15:49,920
They looked for the trait 
and they encouraged it.

710
01:15:50,462 --> 01:15:53,799
Guard dogs, and they 
turned on their masters.

711
01:15:55,676 --> 01:15:57,844
What's that smell?

712
01:15:59,721 --> 01:16:01,515
These are all the bones of gorillas.

713
01:16:01,682 --> 01:16:04,893
- You mean, these are...? 
- No, these are normal gorillas.

714
01:16:07,437 --> 01:16:10,107
- This one's skull was crushed. 
- Feel that?

715
01:16:10,274 --> 01:16:11,441
Feel what?

716
01:16:27,499 --> 01:16:28,959
Hang on!

717
01:16:36,883 --> 01:16:40,262
- Everybody okay? 
- Yeah, let's go.

718
01:16:43,181 --> 01:16:47,060
Don't go this way. It's all caved in. 
God, I'm so glad to see you.

719
01:16:47,185 --> 01:16:51,273
- I was trying to find the mines... 
- Be quiet. Got any flares, Kahega?

720
01:16:51,440 --> 01:16:52,858
Yeah!

721
01:16:55,527 --> 01:16:58,238
- What's making my eyes burn? 
- Sulfur fumes.

722
01:16:58,405 --> 01:17:00,699
Let's hope there's another way out of here.

723
01:17:14,087 --> 01:17:15,505
Careful.

724
01:17:35,734 --> 01:17:40,322
- What the hell...? 
- It's the mines!

725
01:17:40,489 --> 01:17:45,327
"We are watching you." It's the trainers 
talking. The teacher is watching you.

726
01:17:45,827 --> 01:17:47,371
Dead teachers.

727
01:17:52,751 --> 01:17:53,960
Look.

728
01:17:59,091 --> 01:18:03,804
Yes, yes, yes. I knew it was true!

729
01:18:05,222 --> 01:18:09,017
The city of Zinj, the diamonds...

730
01:18:12,646 --> 01:18:17,734
Every word of it was absolutely true.

731
01:18:19,986 --> 01:18:21,738
I'd leave those alone.

732
01:18:28,161 --> 01:18:30,080
- Any other way out of here? 
- Not that I've noticed.

733
01:18:32,791 --> 01:18:35,710
Help me. Fill up everything.

734
01:18:46,346 --> 01:18:49,349
- You've got to get me out of here! 
- Take a number.

735
01:18:49,516 --> 01:18:52,644
- But we're going to be rich! 
- ls that a way out?

736
01:18:52,811 --> 01:18:53,854
Maybe.

737
01:19:28,930 --> 01:19:30,474
Look out!

738
01:19:52,287 --> 01:19:54,623
- Let's go. 
- Stay close together.

739
01:20:01,296 --> 01:20:05,383
- What is it? 
- It's a geode. A giant diamond.

740
01:20:07,093 --> 01:20:10,931
- They cut him off. Kahega! 
- Check if there's a way out back there.

741
01:20:20,398 --> 01:20:21,983
Kahega!

742
01:20:46,716 --> 01:20:48,510
Jeffrey...

743
01:20:50,262 --> 01:20:51,972
Charlie!

744
01:20:53,098 --> 01:20:54,558
Charlie!

745
01:20:55,851 --> 01:20:57,769
- It's him? 
- It's him.

746
01:21:02,857 --> 01:21:04,442
Come on.

747
01:21:18,206 --> 01:21:20,625
- Is there a way out back there? 
- No, nothing.

748
01:21:22,043 --> 01:21:26,131
- We're almost out of rounds. 
- Buy me two minutes.

749
01:21:53,783 --> 01:21:55,035
Let me try.

750
01:21:56,578 --> 01:21:58,079
Aah!

751
01:22:29,486 --> 01:22:31,863
Ugly gorillas. Ugly. Go</i> away.

752
01:22:35,992 --> 01:22:37,994
They don't know what to make of it.

753
01:22:48,755 --> 01:22:52,342
<i>- Amy. 
- Mother. Mother.</i>

754
01:22:57,263 --> 01:23:01,267
- Peter hug <i>Amy.</i> 
- Maternal instinct, long may she reign.

755
01:23:01,434 --> 01:23:04,104
- What are you doing? 
- What am I doing? I'll tell you.

756
01:23:04,229 --> 01:23:06,147
- We're getting out. 
- What about them?

757
01:23:06,314 --> 01:23:09,109
Put them on 
the endangered species list.

758
01:23:16,366 --> 01:23:20,245
Come on, Monroe. Let's go! Move!

759
01:23:20,412 --> 01:23:23,540
- What the hell is that? 
- The latest thing in communication.

760
01:23:23,665 --> 01:23:25,583
- Climb! 
- Up here.

761
01:23:27,585 --> 01:23:30,171
- Go! Go! 
- Come on.

762
01:24:08,376 --> 01:24:09,794
Come on!

763
01:24:16,634 --> 01:24:18,762
Come on, girl. Come on!

764
01:24:29,898 --> 01:24:31,107
GO, Amy!

765
01:24:53,546 --> 01:24:55,423
Keep going!

766
01:24:57,801 --> 01:25:00,512
- Unh. 
- Come on, come on.

767
01:25:04,307 --> 01:25:05,558
Wait!

768
01:25:08,353 --> 01:25:10,063
- Where are they? 
- I don't know.

769
01:25:29,374 --> 01:25:31,000
Hang on!

770
01:25:34,671 --> 01:25:36,548
Watch out!

771
01:25:38,299 --> 01:25:41,094
- Go, Amy! 
- Hurry!

772
01:25:41,261 --> 01:25:44,180
Just hurry! Come on!

773
01:25:52,105 --> 01:25:55,024
- Come on! 
- You can do it!

774
01:25:56,776 --> 01:25:58,069
Keep moving.

775
01:25:59,070 --> 01:26:00,822
Head for higher ground.

776
01:26:01,698 --> 01:26:03,449
Keep going, Amy!

777
01:26:34,147 --> 01:26:37,233
Should be a big yellow case 
with a red stripe on that plane.

778
01:26:37,400 --> 01:26:40,278
It's a balloon. I'll get the transmitter.

779
01:26:42,280 --> 01:26:43,406
Amy!

780
01:26:48,161 --> 01:26:49,829
Amy!

781
01:26:50,914 --> 01:26:53,082
- How close is the border? 
- Not far.

782
01:26:53,249 --> 01:26:55,168
This is Karen Ross, 81452.

783
01:26:55,335 --> 01:27:00,548
That is KR 81452. 
Houston, Travis, do you read?

784
01:27:00,715 --> 01:27:03,801
<i>KR 81452.</i>

785
01:27:03,968 --> 01:27:06,512
Houston, Travis, do you read?

786
01:27:06,721 --> 01:27:13,645
81452, that is KR 81452. 
Houston, Travis, do you read?

787
01:27:15,855 --> 01:27:19,734
- Karen, is that you? 
<i>- It's</i> me, Travis.

788
01:27:19,901 --> 01:27:22,904
I thought I'd lost you. 
I sent another expedition.

789
01:27:23,029 --> 01:27:29,202
<i>- Did</i> you get <i>it?</i> 
- I have bad news. Charles was killed.

790
01:27:29,577 --> 01:27:34,082
Did you get the diamond? Did you?

791
01:27:37,543 --> 01:27:41,673
<i>- Yes.</i> 
- Good girl.

792
01:27:43,883 --> 01:27:49,555
Do you remember when I told you 
that if I ever knew you sent me here...

793
01:27:49,722 --> 01:27:54,519
for some diamond, 
and not for Charlie, I'd make you sorry?

794
01:27:54,978 --> 01:27:57,897
<i>Karen, of course I'm upset.</i>

795
01:27:58,022 --> 01:28:03,152
<i>- But what's done is done. I could...</i> 
- I <i>know. You need</i> a <i>new</i> cash <i>machine.</i>

796
01:28:03,319 --> 01:28:05,029
<i>What would happen to the satellite...</i>

797
01:28:05,196 --> 01:28:08,199
if I put its phone number in the laser 
and pulled the trigger?

798
01:28:08,366 --> 01:28:11,452
The chip from the transmitter's 
got the satellite's number.

799
01:28:15,581 --> 01:28:21,462
It's a 12,000 channel chip. 
If you put it through the diamond... Karen!

800
01:28:26,551 --> 01:28:28,386
This is for you, Charlie.

801
01:28:32,223 --> 01:28:33,641
No!

802
01:28:36,936 --> 01:28:38,229
Amy!

803
01:28:41,232 --> 01:28:42,692
There you are.

804
01:28:51,743 --> 01:28:53,995
Amy, you saved me.

805
01:28:56,581 --> 01:28:58,249
It's okay.

806
01:29:15,933 --> 01:29:17,477
Thank you.

807
01:29:21,564 --> 01:29:23,608
I love you, too.

808
01:29:25,568 --> 01:29:27,111
Mother?

809
01:29:30,573 --> 01:29:33,242
Oh, I see. It's Africa. It's your mother.

810
01:29:35,244 --> 01:29:38,331
Amy, where did you go?

811
01:29:40,208 --> 01:29:43,711
Good gorillas? What good gorillas?

812
01:29:52,178 --> 01:29:53,429
Handsome fella.

813
01:30:19,288 --> 01:30:20,748
Amy...

814
01:30:27,380 --> 01:30:29,924
Look at that. 
ls that Amy with the...?

815
01:30:30,091 --> 01:30:33,761
The silverback. So she's...

816
01:30:35,763 --> 01:30:38,808
I see. I see.

817
01:30:43,020 --> 01:30:44,897
She's home.

818
01:31:02,206 --> 01:31:04,584
- Will she be all right? 
- They know what to do.

819
01:31:04,750 --> 01:31:06,043
It's us I'm worried about.

820
01:31:06,210 --> 01:31:09,797
- We've got to go. Come on. 
- Bye, Amy.

821
01:31:44,916 --> 01:31:47,501
- Peter, would you do me a favor? 
- What?

822
01:31:47,668 --> 01:31:49,587
Would you throw this away for me.

823
01:31:50,379 --> 01:31:52,048
You sure?

824
01:31:55,259 --> 01:31:56,260
Ouch.

825
01:32:02,892 --> 01:32:06,646
- There's a wind. 
- I hope it blows us someplace good.

826
01:32:06,812 --> 01:32:08,439
Me too.

